HEADWORD: Bescatter
<hw>Be*scat"ter</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To scatter over.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To cover sparsely by scattering (something); to
